brief_summary.textblock:
      Primary Objective:

      Assess effectiveness of insulin glargine (U300) in achieving glycemic goal measured by
      hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c).

      Secondary Objectives:

        -  Assess effectiveness in achieving glycemic goal measured by HbA1c;

        -  Assess effectiveness on change in HbA1c, fasting plasma glucose (FPG) and self-monitored
           plasma glucose (SMPG) ;

        -  Assess requirement for intensification of therapy by additional antidiabetics.

        -  Assess incidence of hypoglycemia;

        -  Assess other safety endpoints: adverse events (AEs), serious adverse events (SAEs);

        -  Assess change in body weight.

criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria :

          -  Signed patient informed consent;

          -  Type 2 diabetes mellitus;

          -  Treated with at least 1 oral antidiabetic drug (OAD) for at least 6 months;

          -  Hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c) >7.0 % and ≤11% within 3 months of study baseline;

          -  Physicians' decision in accordance with the current local guidelines to add basal
             insulin glargine U300 to an existing OAD regimen

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  Diabetes mellitus other than type 2;

          -  Contraindication to insulin glargine U300 according to local product labelling;

        The above information is not intended to contain all considerations relevant to a patient's
        potential participation in a clinical trial.
